Dear Hardik and Team,

I'm really proud of your effort. Thank you for giving us an electrifying, spine-tingling performance that was full of euphoria and goosebumps. I couldn't be grateful enough. Thank you for making us believe that India could play a Gold Medal match again after 1980.

As a fan, I take responsibility for not caring about this sport earlier. This sport is an emotion for all of us, but I promise we will rebuild as a nation and regain our heritage. The Hockey India League will be a big success, we will make it big and better together, and we will contribute & fullfill our dreams of lifting the Gold Medal together.

As the Paris Olympics continue to delight and amaze, here's an article in praise of intercultural dialogue and Franglais... As Euronews set out, hybrid languages are a key part of cultural integration.

Also known as “macaronic language”, some of the best known early examples were when Latin merged with local vernacular languages in Europe: "While Latin was still the go-to language for religion and academia in the 12th century, vernacular language was becoming increasingly popular for poetry and storytelling, and writers started to combine the two in their works."

Euronews say that "Macaronic” itself comes a combination of Neo-Latin and Italian, from the peasant pasta (although others say it is more of a dumpling) that inspired the 15th century Padua poet Tifi Odasi’s work ‘Macaronea’ which used macarnoic language.

Today, some of the most common macaronic languages in Europe are combinations of local languages and English (Frenglish/Franglais etc), owing to the cultural prevalence of English as a global lingua franca.

'Loan words', hybridisation and macaronic language keep refreshing and updating languages - and help us share the best of different cultures.

🥉 Olympic Men's Football Bronze Medal Match: Egypt vs. Morocco 

Despite a 3-1 extra-time defeat to host nation France, Egypt stands on the brink of winning their first Olympic football medal. They face Morocco, who previously beat them in the U23 Africa Cup of Nations final last summer.

The Pharaohs 🇪🇬 have a habit of starting strong, leading in three of their last four Olympic matches. However, their defense has struggled, failing to keep a clean sheet in their last three games. Coach Rogério Micale is determined to secure an Olympic medal, motivating his team to hold their lead if they strike first.

Morocco's 🇲🇦 semi-final story was similar; they led against Spain but lost 2-1. With no extra-time in their game, Morocco should be fresher. Despite internal conflicts with coach Walid Regragui, Morocco aims for their first Olympic medal, showing second-half vulnerabilities by conceding most goals after the break.
